Problem: Regular octagon $ABCDEFGH$ has its center at $J$.  Each of the vertices and the center are to be associated with one of the digits $1$ through $9$, with each digit used once, in such a way that the sums of the numbers on the lines $AJE$, $BJF$, $CJG$, and $DJH$ are all equal.  In how many ways can this be done?
[asy]
pair A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,J;
A=(20,20(2+sqrt(2)));
B=(20(1+sqrt(2)),20(2+sqrt(2)));
C=(20(2+sqrt(2)),20(1+sqrt(2)));
